# Gabriel Toth Portfolio - Cursor Rules

## Project

Gabriel Toth Gonçalves Personal Portfolio - Full Stack Developer
Website: <https://www.gabrieltoth.com>

## Tech Stack

- **Framework**: Next.js 16 (App Router) + React 19 + TypeScript 6
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS 4 + shadcn/ui (new-york, RSC enabled)
- **Icons**: lucide-react
- **Internationalization**: next-intl (4 locales: en, pt-BR, es, de; default pt-BR)
- **Authentication**: Custom Argon2id (no Supabase Auth)
- **Database**: Supabase Postgres (Free plan)
- **Email**: Resend (Free plan)
- **Deployment**: Vercel + Cloudflare
- **Social integrations**: YouTube, Instagram, Facebook, TikTok, Kick

## Language Policy

- **PRIMARY LANGUAGE**: English (ALL code, comments, documentation, commits)
- **Code**: All variables, functions, classes, comments MUST be in English
- **Documentation**: README, comments, JSDoc - ALL in English
- **Git**: Commit messages, branch names, PR descriptions - ALL in English
- **Portuguese**: ONLY for user-facing content translations (i18n files)

## Code Rules

### Formatting

- **Indentation**: 4 spaces (ALWAYS)
- **Quotes**: Double for ALL strings AND JSX (see .prettierrc.json)
- **Semicolon**: Never (Prettier strips them)
- **Trailing comma**: Always in multi-line objects/arrays

### File Structure

```
src/
├── app/
│   ├── [locale]/               # Internationalized routes
│   │   ├── login/              # Custom Argon2id login
│   │   ├── register/           # Multi-step registration
│   │   ├── reset-password/     # Token-based reset (password_reset_tokens table)
│   │   ├── dashboard/          # Dashboard + publish
│   │   └── settings/           # Preferences, Security, Billing
│   ├── api/
│   │   ├── auth/               # login, register, forgot-password, reset-password
│   │   ├── oauth/callback/     # Instagram, Facebook, TikTok, YouTube
│   │   ├── youtube/            # link/start, link/callback, upload
│   │   ├── posts/              # CRUD posts
│   │   ├── contact/            # Contact form
│   │   └── platform/           # Webhooks (Stripe — shell only)
│   ├── globals.css
│   └── layout.tsx
├── components/
│   ├── ui/                     # shadcn/ui primitives
│   ├── layout/                 # Header, Footer
│   ├── publish/                # PostingInterface, Calendar, Scheduler
│   ├── settings/               # PreferencesSection, SecuritySection, BillingSection
│   └── auth/                   # GoogleLogoutButton, EmailAuthForm
├── lib/
│   ├── middleware/              # context, csrf-protection, security-headers
│   ├── supabase/               # client.ts, server.ts (simplified, no @supabase/ssr)
│   ├── auth/                   # unified-auth, email-service, temp-token, rate-limiter
│   ├── stripe/                 # Config only (no active API routes)
│   ├── cache/                  # @upstash/redis client
│   ├── shutdown/               # Graceful shutdown (ioredis — legacy Docker)
│   ├── retry/                  # Retry wrappers (ioredis — legacy Docker)
│   ├── audit/                  # Audit logger (TODO)
│   ├── posting/                # Social platform adapters (Facebook, Twitter, LinkedIn)
│   ├── queue/                  # Background processor
│   ├── oauth/                  # State signer (HMAC, not Redis)
│   ├── facebook/               # Facebook Pages integration
│   └── tiktok/                 # TikTok integration
├── i18n/
│   ├── en/                     # English (JSON files)
│   ├── pt-BR/                  # Portuguese (JSON files)
│   ├── es/                     # Spanish (JSON files)
│   └── de/                     # German (JSON files)
├── __tests__/
│   ├── security/               # 55+ attack matrix test files
│   ├── auth/                   # Auth flow tests
│   ├── integration/            # Integration tests
│   ├── lib/                    # Lib unit tests
│   └── token-killer/           # Standalone tool tests
└── token-killer/               # Standalone CLI tool (embedded, uses Express)
```

### React Components

- **Always use TypeScript** with well-defined interfaces
- **Function components** with arrow functions
- **Props destructuring** in function parameters
- **Export default** at the end of file
- **Component names** in PascalCase
- **File names** in kebab-case
- **ALL NAMES IN ENGLISH** - no Portuguese variable/function names

### Component Example

```tsx
interface HeroSectionProps {
    title: string
    description: string
}

const HeroSection = ({ title, description }: HeroSectionProps) => {
    return (
        <section className="min-h-screen flex items-center justify-center">
            <div className="text-center">
                <h1 className="text-4xl font-bold">{title}</h1>
                <p className="text-lg text-muted-foreground">{description}</p>
            </div>
        </section>
    )
}

export default HeroSection
```

### Internationalization

- **Always use** translation functions
- **Keys organized** hierarchically
- **Fallbacks** for missing translations
- **Consistency** between languages
- **Translation keys** in English (snake_case or dot.notation)

### Tailwind CSS

- **Mobile-first** approach
- **Design tokens** from shadcn/ui
- **Utility classes** preferred
- **Custom components** when necessary
- **Dark mode** supported

### Performance

- **Next.js Image** for all images
- **Lazy loading** for heavy sections
- **Dynamic imports** when appropriate
- **SEO optimization** with metadata

### Git & Commits (ENGLISH ONLY)

- **Commit format**: `type: short description`
- **Commit body**: Detailed description when needed
- **Example**:

    ```
    feat: add hero section with responsive design

    - Implement hero section component with TypeScript
    - Add responsive design for mobile and desktop
    - Include animation effects with Tailwind CSS
    - Add proper SEO meta tags for hero content
    ```

- **Types**: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, test, chore
- **Branch naming**: `feature/component-name`, `fix/issue-description`
- **ALL ENGLISH**: No Portuguese in commit messages, branch names, or PR descriptions

### Best Practices

1. **Accessibility**: Always consider a11y
2. **Responsiveness**: Mobile-first design
3. **SEO**: Meta tags and structured data
4. **Performance**: Core Web Vitals
5. **Maintainability**: Clean and documented code

### Allowed Libraries

- shadcn/ui (components)
- lucide-react (icons)
- clsx + tailwind-merge (conditional classes, cn utility)
- next-intl (i18n)
- next-auth (authentication)
- @supabase/supabase-js (database)
- argon2 (password hashing, LGPD compliance)
- googleapis (YouTube)
- @upstash/ratelimit + @upstash/redis (rate limiting + cache)
- resend (email)
- react-icons + @icons-pack/react-simple-icons (social icons)
- date-fns + date-fns-tz (dates)
- uplot (charts)
- class-variance-authority (shadcn/ui dependency)
- commander (token-killer CLI only)

### Avoid

- Unnecessary CSS-in-JS
- Heavy libraries without justification
- Untyped components
- Magic numbers/strings
- Duplicated code
- Portuguese in code/comments (except i18n content)

## Development Environment

- No mandatory local infrastructure for most tasks.
- `npm run dev` starts Next.js dev server on port 3000.
- For DB-dependent tests: ensure `DATABASE_URL` is set (local Postgres or Supabase remote).
- For full integration tests that need Supabase local: `docker compose up -d` in `docker/` + `npx supabase start` (optional).

## Attack Matrix (Security Tests)

Every API route MUST have an attack matrix comment and corresponding tests. Categories that apply must be enumerated before writing tests:

| # | Category | What to test |
|---|----------|-------------|
| 1 | **Auth bypass** | null/expired/invalid session, non-existent user |
| 2 | **HTTP method confusion** | POST on GET route, GET on POST route |
| 3 | **Type attacks** | string, number, boolean, null, array, object, NaN, Infinity, undefined |
| 4 | **Value attacks** | negative, zero, empty string, whitespace-only, max boundary |
| 5 | **Structure attacks** | missing fields, extra fields, empty `{}`, array `[]`, null body |
| 6 | **Prototype pollution** | `__proto__`, `constructor.prototype` |
| 7 | **Injection** | SQL, XSS, command injection, NoSQL operators (`$ne`, `$gt`) |
| 8 | **Unicode/encoding** | emoji, null byte `\0`, control chars, RTL override |
| 9 | **Size attacks** | 10k+ strings, 100+ level nesting, duplicate keys, JSON bomb |
| 10 | **Rate limiting** | within limit, exceeded limit, burst, reset |
| 11 | **CSRF** | missing token, expired token, wrong session |
| 12 | **Race conditions** | concurrent duplicates, TOCTOU, parallel mutations |
| 13 | **Content-Type** | wrong/missing Content-Type, multipart, charset confusion |
| 14 | **HTTP header** | smuggling, host override, X-Forwarded-For spoofing |
| 15 | **Info disclosure** | stack traces, internal paths, user enumeration, timing |
| 16 | **Business logic** | self-grant, replay, insufficient funds bypass |
| 17 | **IDOR** | change ID/email in params/body to access other users |
| 18 | **Path traversal** | `../`, `..\\`, absolute paths |
| 19 | **Mass assignment** | extra body fields mapping to DB columns |
| 20 | **SSRF** | URL params that make server fetch external resources |
| 21 | **Timing side-channel** | measurable response time differences |

**Rule**: Write comment `// Attack matrix: 1,3,4,5` (applicable rows) before each route, then one `it()` per variant. Omit only with `// SKIP: reason`.

## Social Platform Integrations

- **Facebook**: `src/lib/facebook/` — Pages API, OAuth, publish, webhooks, analytics
- **Instagram**: `src/app/api/oauth/callback/instagram/` — OAuth callback, HMAC state signer
- **TikTok**: `src/lib/tiktok/` — OAuth, publish, analytics, webhooks
- **YouTube**: `src/app/api/youtube/` — OAuth linking (start/callback), upload
- **Kick**: (basic config exists)

## Useful Commands

```bash
npm run dev          # Development (Turbopack, port 3000)
npm run build        # Production build (does NOT type-check)
npm run type-check   # tsc --noEmit on tsconfig.json + tsconfig.test.json
npm run lint         # ESLint on src/**/*.{ts,tsx}
npm run format       # Prettier write
npm run format:check # Prettier check
npm run spell-check  # CSpell on source files
npm run test         # Vitest (unit/component)
npm run test:all     # Full CI gate: type-check → lint → format:check → spell-check → test
npm run test:e2e     # Playwright E2E (auto-starts dev server)
```

